-- Liverpool, Spurs Mull Bids for Barca’s Roberto: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-11-05T08:34:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-05/liverpool-spurs-mull-bids-for-barca-s-roberto-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet links.  Race for Roberto  Liverpool and Tottenham Hotspur may bid as much as 20
million euros ($27 million) for Barcelona midfielder Sergi
Roberto, the  Daily Star reported .  AC Milan also has made contact with the Spanish club about
the 21-year-old, the newspaper added.  Magpies Midfielder  Newcastle United midfielder Yohan Cabaye is wanted by
Italian Serie A leader Roma, which would pay 12 million pounds
($19.1 million) for the Frenchman, the  Daily Mirror reported .  Roma wants to add a central midfielder in January and will
turn to Tottenham duo Sandro and Lewis Holtby if it can’t bring
in Cabaye, the newspaper said.  Wenger Waits  Arsenal manager  Arsene Wenger  will delay signing an
extension to his current 7.5 million-pound contract until the
Gunners have qualified for the Champions League knockout stages,
the  Daily Mail reported .  Wenger, 64, doesn’t want negotiations to become a
distraction during a difficult run of games, the Mail added.  Gunners Monitor Grenier  Arsenal hasn’t given up on adding Lyon midfielder Clement
Grenier in January, the  Daily Express reported .  The Gunners are continuing to monitor the 22-year-old even
after he rejected a 6 million-pound move in the offseason and
signed a new contract with Lyon, the Express added.  Editor: Alex Duff  To contact the reporter on this story:
